snippet: Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan, seeking to retain power despite a term limit in his current post, took 52 percent of the vote, according to unofficial results.
abstract: Unofficial results of Turkey's presidential vote show Prime Min Recep Tayyip Erdogan winner with 52 percent of vote, highest percentage in his political career; Ekmeleddin Ihsanoglu, candidate of main secular and nationalist parties, receives 38 percent.

byline.original: By CEYLAN YEGINSU and SEBNEM ARSU
byline.contributor: Ceylan Yeginsu reported from Istanbul, and Sebnem Arsu from Ankara, Turkey.

lead_paragraph: Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan, seeking to retain power despite a term limit in his current post, took 52 percent of the vote, according to unofficial results.

headline.main: Turkey’s Premier Is Proclaimed Winner of Presidential Election
headline.print_headline: Turkey’s Premier Is Proclaimed Presidential Victor
